<bug>
    <id>268892</id>
    <title>Command-w (Ctrl+W) does not close Element Properties window</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.7.5) Gecko/20041107 Firefox/1.0
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.7.5) Gecko/20041107 Firefox/1.0</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If you get Properties using the contextual menu, on a image, command-w on the
keyboard should close the window.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">It does not, however the File menu in the
menubar flashes, but nothing happens.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">Closing the window with the close button
works of course.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">1 right-click on a image, choose "Properties"</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">2 view properties window</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">3 press command-w on the keyboard</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Actual Results:  
Nothing.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">File menu in menubar flashes, but the window goes nowhere.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Expected Results:  
The window should have closed.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
